9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 686, L.D. 1057, “Resolve, to Aid
10 Municipalities, Animal Control Officers and Other Parties in Complying with Electronic
11 Dog Licensing Requirements”
12 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, to Aid Municipalities in Complying with Dog Licensing Database
14 Requirements'
15 Amend the resolve by striking out all of the emergency preamble.
16 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
17 'Sec. 1. Moratorium. Resolved: That the Department of Agriculture,
18 Conservation and Forestry may not require a municipality to participate in the dog licensing
19 database as provided in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 7, section 3925 or to implement
20 PetPoint software or any other data management platform for the purpose of tracking
21 licenses for dogs until one year following the effective date of this section; during this time,
22 the department shall allow municipalities to use alternative methods for the purposes of
23 tracking dog licenses.'
24 Amend the resolve in section 2 in the 4th line (page 1, line 27 in L.D.) by striking out
25 the following: "issuance" and inserting the following: 'tracking'
26 Amend the resolve by inserting after section 2 the following:
27 'Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
28 appropriations and allocations are made.
29 AGRICULTURE, CONSERVATION AND FORESTRY, DEPARTMENT OF
30 Animal Welfare Fund 0946
31 Initiative: Provides funding for contracted services.
