22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, removes the
2244 emergency preamble and emergency clause from the resolve and changes the title. It
2255 corrects a cross-reference in the resolve. The amendment provides that for a period of one
2266 year following the effective date of this legislation the Department of Agriculture,
2277 Conservation and Forestry may not require a municipality to participate in the dog licensing
2288 database as provided in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 7, section 3925 or to implement
2299 PetPoint software or any other data management platform. The amendment also adds an
3300 appropriations and allocations section.
